Remove unused variables (issue #7)

Updates to allow for cross compiling without make producing errors.

The previous suggested solution of utilising conditionals does not appear to resolve this issue.

This will allow for easier deployment via brew on OS X.

The proposed solution has been taken from this suggested answer at Stack Overvflow: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/714100/os-detecting-makefile/14777895#14777895

I have tested this on:
  * OS X El Capitan
  * CentOS Linux release 7.1.1503
  * Ubuntu 14.04.4 LTS

Allow cross-compiling connect

When cross-compiling e.g. on Linux for Windows, we need a way to tell
GNU make to avoid running `ver` (because that does not exist on Linux).
Likewise, the `UNAME` variable needs to be set explicitly via the
command-line if one wants to cross-compile for other platforms.

So let's make the `UNAME` and `WINVER` definitions conditional.

Signed-off-by: Johannes Schindelin <johannes.schindelin@gmx.de>
